5 Sec. 2. 29 V.S.A. § 173 is added to read:
6 § 173. VERMONT STATE BUILDING SECURITY BOARD
7 (a) The Vermont State Building Security Board is established to oversee
8 the safety and security of worksites for Vermont State employees and the
9 employees of the Judiciary.
10 (b)(1) The Board shall consist of the following seven members:
11 (A) two members, appointed by the Governor;
12 (B) the Vermont State Court Administrator or designee;
13 (C) one member, appointed by the Attorney General; and
14 (D) three members, appointed by the President of the Vermont State
15 Employees’ Association.
16 (2) The Board shall annually, from among its membership, elect a
17 member to serve as Board chair and a member to serve as Board vice chair.
18 (3) The members of the Board shall serve terms of six years and may
19 serve not more than two consecutive terms. All appointments shall be made
20 between January 1 and February 1 of each odd-numbered year, except to fill a
21 vacancy. Members shall serve until their successors are appointed.
