1 Sec. 3. 29 V.S.A. § 174 is added to read:
2 § 174. BUILDINGS AND COURTHOUSES POLICE DEPARTMENT
3 (a) Definitions. As used in this section:
4 (1) “Courthouse” means a building or any portion of a building
5 designated by the Supreme Court of Vermont as a courthouse.
6 (2) “State building” means a building or any portion of a building
7 designated by the Director of Safety and Security, in consultation with the
8 Commissioner of Buildings and General Services, as a State building.
9 (b) Creation. The Buildings and Courthouses Police Department is created
10 within the Department of Public Safety. The Commissioner of Public Safety
11 shall appoint and may remove, at the Commissioner’s pleasure, a Buildings
12 and Courthouses Police Department officer to serve as Chief. The Chief shall
13 be an exempt State employee and shall appoint individuals to serve as
14 additional Buildings and Courthouses Police Department officers. All such
15 positions shall be classified State employees. The Chief shall supervise the
16 officer force. Such appointments and all oaths or affirmations shall be in
17 writing and filed with the Commissioner of Public Safety.
18 (c) Powers; training.
19 (1) A Buildings and Courthouses Police Department officer shall have
20 all the same powers and authority as sheriffs and other law enforcement
21 officers anywhere in the State, which shall include the authority to arrest
